<br>
He finds himself in the gardens of the hall of the Elven Elite, but he finds himself hiding in the shadows.  He realizes that his heart is what really is in shadow.  He knows that he must now make a choice and let all be settled by it.  He heads from the gardens in search of the Grand Moff.<br>
<br>
He enters via the window, undetected by Aryllyian.  He clears his throat as he approaches the desk.  “Sir Aryllyian, I must speak to you regarding the troubles of my heart,” Myrrer begins.<br>
<br>
“In the past several days I have felt a pull to do that which you and those of the Elite will find most horrific and I am not certain of my course.  I ask that you listen to my story and think upon my dilemma.  Then I ask your advice.”<br>
<br>
At Aryllyian’s nod Myrrer continues, “Good knight, I have felt a recent pull to enter an area forbidden by the oath I have sworn as a member of the Elven Elite.  I am not sorry, that I cannot find fault with my desire to enter the gardens of the Goddess and take its dweller’s life.  She after all is not the one I worship.  However, I am not an oath breaker and no person shall be able to state otherwise.<br>
<br>
“You are my oldest friend of the membership and you know I have the heart of a rogue, but not a black heart at all.  My troubles are in the conflict of oath versus a pull that I believe comes from Bristlebane himself.  It would be simple if that was the sole conflict, but a greater one arises, as here is my home, my friends and those I’d die for above any calling.  And I do not wish to depart this hall.”<br>
<br>
“Please do not respond immediately but think upon this for me, I shall in the meantime seek out others for their guidance.<br>
<br>
Myrrer exits through the door and seeks out Vladimirski, Seyah, Rokken, Firinn and Craw and relays his dilemma to them, parting with the same request, “Think upon this for a time and allow me to wander the lands and consider this further.  I vow to not break my oath until I have had your council.”<br>
<br>
As he exits the Guild Hall, Myrrer looks back and wonders if this, his only home, will still welcome him when next he returns… <br>
