<br>
He recalls, glumly, the argument he had with Myrrer, begging him not to follow this path.  If Craw had a practical, rational side, he would have realized that Myrrer must follow his heart and do what he believes to be right.  However, as we all know, Dwarves are neither practical or rational.<br>
